<TITLE> HC orders Falu release </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)  Former BNP lawmaker Mosaddek Hossain Falu faces no bar to his freedom as the High Court, granting bail in the last case against him, also declared his detention illegal on Thursday, a lawyer for the BNP leader told bdnews24.com. A HC bench of justices Mir Hasmot Ali and Shamim Hasnain ordered Falu to be released in the event of no case against him, upon a writ petition by Falu's lawyer challenging the legality of his detention. "The High Court issued Falu's release order, ruling his further detention as illegal," said Advocate Ahsanul Karim, who represented Falu in court. In the meantime, a separate bench granted two-month bail to Falu in a case involving misappropriation of relief materials for the poor. b
